Evil Tomato - Mohit Cheppudira <mohit@muthanna.com>
A portable shared shell environment.

Setup
-----

1) Clone this repo (You may want to fork it first.)

Read/Write:
$ git clone git@github.com:0xfe/evil.git

Read-Only HTTP:
$ git clone http://github.com/0xfe/evil.git

2) Set EVIL_HOME to the base directory of this repo env.sh.

export EVIL_HOME=~/s

3) Source dotfiles/bashrc.include.sh into your bashrc. You can add your
customizations to that file (e.g., in setup_mac).

source ~/s/env.sh
source $EVIL_HOME/dotfiles/bashrc.include.sh
setup_mac

4) Symlink to the other configuration files.

$ ln -s $EVIL_HOME/dotfiles/screenrc .screenrc
$ ln -s $EVIL_HOME/dotfiles/vimrc .vimrc

5) Add the relevant cronjobs to your crontab.

$ crontab -e
(Edit crontab)

$ crontab -l
0,15,30,45 * * * * ~/s/cron/update_local_repositories.sh >/dev/null 2>&1
